channel.description:
[center][b][u][size=24pt]PART 1: SPAWNING AN NPC[/size][/u][/b][/center]

[center]In order to start a dialogue you will first need to spawn a character![/center]
[center]So lets add an npc called "Spirit"[/center]

[center]Open up [b]NPCSpawning.java[/b][/center]

[center]Now under:
[code=java]	public static void spawnNPCS() {[/code]

Add this:
[code=java]		World.spawnNPC(13482, new WorldTile(X_COORD, Y_COORD, 0), -1, false, true);[/code]
The 13482 is the NPC ID that we are going to use. Now replace the following [b]X_COORD[/b] and [b]Y_COORD[/b] with your custom npc spawn coordinates. All you are doing is spawning an npc at that position and telling it not to move because of the [b]false[/b] statement. If you want it to move then simply replace [b]false[/b] with [b]true[/b].

[center][b]NOW SAVE AND COMPILE TO MAKE SURE THERE IS NO ERROR![/b][/center]
[center][b]IF THERE IS NO ERROR THEN RUN YOUR SERVER TO SEE IF THE SPIRIT NPC IS THERE![b][/center]
[center][b]IF THE NPC IS THERE THEN GO TO PART 2![b][center]




[center][b][u][size=24pt]PART 2: ADDING THE DIALOUGE[/size][/u][/b][/center]

[center]Now the dialogue is the most difficult part. I too had troubles with it until I realized what I was doing wrong. Mostly bracket errors, but I found an easier way. I will explain it later. [/center]

[center]Create a new java file and save it as [b]Spirit.java[/b][/center]

[center]Now inside [b]Spirit.java[/b] add this:[/center]
[center][code=java]package com.rs.game.player.dialogues;

import com.rs.Settings;
