[center]Ok everything you need to know is in the code, I kinda got lazy towards the end because it was fucking anoying coping and pasting[/center]

[center]Now open up NPCHandler.java and look for:
[code=java]				npc.faceEntity(player);
				if (!player.getControlerManager().processNPCClick1(npc))
					return;[/code]

under it add:
[code=java]				if (npc.getId() == 13482)
					player.getDialogueManager().startDialogue("Spirit",
							npc.getId());[/code]

What this does is telling the server to open [b]Spirit.java[/b] on the first click. If there is already and "if" statement below yours then simply add "else" before the if on the one below yours if there isn't already one.

Now open up [b]DialogueHandler.java[/b] and look for:
[code=java]	public static final void init() {
		try {[/code]

under it add:
[code=java]			Class<Dialogue> value43 = (Class<Dialogue>) Class
					.forName(Spirit.class.getCanonicalName());
			handledDialogues.put("Spirit", value43);[/code]

Don't ask me what this is exactly suppose to do because I don't know, but all I know is that it helps open up [b]Spirit.java[/b]. Plus it gives you no error when compiling this. 
[b]NOW SAVE AND COMPILE AND TEST OUT YOUR NEW TALKING NPC! :D[/b][/center]
